THE SA Football Association (Safa) says they will be guided by national government on what steps to take after the first Coronavirus case was confirmed in Kwa-Zulu Natal. “Safa, like any other entity, is guided by the National Government on such matters,” Safa spokesman Dominc Chimhavi told the media yesterday. Durban is host to Absa Premiershp matches, GladAfrica Championships and Maritzburg United will tonight host Polokwane City at the Harry Gwala Stadium, both in the PSL and Diski Challenge, while the Sugar Ray Xulu Stadium will be home to Golden Arrows who will host Soweto giants Orlando Pirates tomorrow. In the GladAfrica Championship, Real Kings will host Jomo Cosmos at Chartsworth Stadium and Umhlathuze Sports Complex will see Richards Bay and Royal Eagles cross swords. In the Super Rugby, the Sharks will host Jaguares at the Jonsson Kings Park Stadiu tomorrow afternoon. On Thursday Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize confirmed the first positive test case for the Covid-19 coronavirus on 38-year-old man who travelled to Italy with his wife. Mkhize released a statement on Thursday confirming that the National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NCID) confirmed a positive test. While it was not clear at which port of entry the patient landed, Mkhize said that a tracer team has been deployed to KwaZulu-Natal. The man is now self-isolated.  First coronavirus case confirmed in South Africahttps://t.co/Zu8dDWH07p   